WEBVTT

1
00:00:02.794 --> 00:00:05.005
[ Saucer whirs ]

2
00:00:06.548 --> 00:00:08.634
-This the place?
-This the place.

3
00:00:10.135 --> 00:00:11.637
[ Grunts ]

4
00:00:11.678 --> 00:00:12.804
[ Machine beeps ]

5
00:00:12.846 --> 00:00:14.348
-This the stuff?
-This the stuff.

6
00:00:14.431 --> 00:00:16.183
And this is no ordinary stuff.
Morty.

7
00:00:16.266 --> 00:00:18.727
This sap is <i>primo</i> .

8
00:00:18.810 --> 00:00:20.312
[ Both grunting ]

9
00:00:20.354 --> 00:00:22.439
[ Liquid sloshes ]

10
00:00:22.481 --> 00:00:24.650
[ Vines creak ]

11
00:00:24.691 --> 00:00:25.984
-Argh!
-Ah!

12
00:00:26.026 --> 00:00:27.986
-What the hell?
-Shit! Vines!

13
00:00:28.028 --> 00:00:29.321
[ Both grunting ]

14
00:00:29.363 --> 00:00:33.075
Locusts come
to harvest my bounty.

15
00:00:33.158 --> 00:00:34.785
Hey. giant ancient tree guy.

16
00:00:34.826 --> 00:00:37.329
Sorry. We thought
the sap was accountability free.

17
00:00:37.412 --> 00:00:40.541
Yeah. well. we're not locusts.
just a couple adventurers.

18
00:00:40.624 --> 00:00:42.834
Spacefarers.

19
00:00:42.876 --> 00:00:44.795
You consume your planets.

20
00:00:44.836 --> 00:00:48.590
then spread your sickness
to the stars.

21
00:00:48.674 --> 00:00:50.968
Nah. Nah. man.
We're clean. I promise.

22
00:00:51.009 --> 00:00:52.177
Yeah. yeah.
We just got tested.

23
00:00:52.261 --> 00:00:54.137
and I got a bit of
a soy allergy.

24
00:00:54.179 --> 00:00:57.975
I have a place
for animals like you.

25
00:00:58.016 --> 00:01:01.728
You will be reformed.

26
00:01:01.812 --> 00:01:04.690
[ Groaning ]

27
00:01:01.812 --> 00:01:04.690
[ Groaning ]

28
00:01:04.731 --> 00:01:06.567
What is...

29
00:01:06.650 --> 00:01:13.907
{\an8}♪♪

30
00:01:13.991 --> 00:01:21.790
{\an8}♪♪

31
00:01:21.873 --> 00:01:23.542
[ Water splashes ]

32
00:01:23.625 --> 00:01:25.043
...this?!

33
00:01:25.127 --> 00:01:26.169
Yeah. Morty.

34
00:01:26.211 --> 00:01:27.713
Not ideal.

35
00:01:27.754 --> 00:01:29.590
But I promise you.
the sap will be worth it.

36
00:01:29.673 --> 00:01:32.467
I had the craziest night
on this stuff a few weeks ago.

37
00:01:32.551 --> 00:01:42.477
{\an8}♪♪

38
00:01:42.561 --> 00:01:51.570
{\an8}♪♪

39
00:01:51.612 --> 00:02:00.203
{\an8}♪♪

40
00:02:00.245 --> 00:02:02.497
{\an8}[ Electricity hisses ]

41
00:02:04.249 --> 00:02:05.792
I'm all wobbly. Rick.

42
00:02:05.876 --> 00:02:06.918
What the fuck's going on.

43
00:02:07.002 --> 00:02:08.920
{\an8}In the same position you are.

44
00:02:09.004 --> 00:02:10.839
{\an8}But I can guess that those roots
extracted the biological data

45
00:02:10.922 --> 00:02:13.592
{\an8}we think of as our minds
and reincarnated us as amoeba.

46
00:02:13.675 --> 00:02:15.594
{\an8}How do we get our
old bodies back?

47
00:02:15.636 --> 00:02:17.471
{\an8}Well.
that's the wrong question.

48
00:02:17.554 --> 00:02:19.431
{\an8}But it's the one all
new cellmates ask.

49
00:02:19.514 --> 00:02:21.433
{\an8}[ Laughs ] "Cellmates."

50
00:02:21.516 --> 00:02:23.685
We use humor to stay sane
in this place.

51
00:02:23.769 --> 00:02:24.936
Yes. sir.

52
00:02:25.020 --> 00:02:26.313
Many folks have tried
to raid this planet

53
00:02:26.396 --> 00:02:27.773
and ended up down here.

54
00:02:27.856 --> 00:02:29.191
Growth and rebirth.

55
00:02:29.232 --> 00:02:30.400
The ball and chain
around our ankles.

56
00:02:30.442 --> 00:02:32.653
{\an8}In here. a man can truly change.

57
00:02:32.736 --> 00:02:34.905
{\an8}But don't mistake that
for freedom.

58
00:02:34.946 --> 00:02:37.157
Give me your cytoplasm.
you limp-dick motherfucker!

59
00:02:37.240 --> 00:02:38.200
[ Yells ]

60
00:02:38.283 --> 00:02:39.451
[ Squish ]

61
00:02:39.493 --> 00:02:40.577
Argh!

62
00:02:40.619 --> 00:02:41.620
[ Grunts ]

63
00:02:41.703 --> 00:02:43.830
[ Slurps ]

64
00:02:45.123 --> 00:02:46.833
[ Water splashes ]

65
00:02:46.917 --> 00:02:48.126
{\an8}What?

66
00:02:46.917 --> 00:02:48.126
{\an8}Huh.

67
00:02:48.168 --> 00:02:49.461
{\an8}Guess if you die.
you start over.

68
00:02:49.544 --> 00:02:51.129
{\an8}Good thing
we hadn't made much progress.

69
00:02:51.171 --> 00:02:52.464
{\an8}Try not to die. Morty.

70
00:02:52.506 --> 00:02:53.799
{\an8}Hello. my delicious friends.

71
00:02:53.882 --> 00:02:54.966
{\an8}He's multicellular now!

72
00:02:55.050 --> 00:02:56.301
{\an8}Back for
another helping?

73
00:02:56.385 --> 00:02:57.594
{\an8}Spawn-camping piece of shit!

74
00:02:57.636 --> 00:02:59.346
{\an8}[ Grunts. gurgles ]

75
00:02:57.636 --> 00:02:59.346
{\an8}Jesus!

76
00:02:59.429 --> 00:03:01.181
{\an8}Prison rules. Morty.
Get to the top of the food chain

77
00:03:01.264 --> 00:03:02.349
{\an8}or you're someone's dinner.

78
00:03:02.432 --> 00:03:03.809
{\an8}[ Grunts. slurps ]

79
00:03:03.850 --> 00:03:05.477
{\an8}Hey. get in here.
We need the nutrients.

80
00:03:05.560 --> 00:03:06.311
{\an8}[ Slurps ]

81
00:03:06.395 --> 00:03:08.563
{\an8}Oh. it's like salty tapioca.

82
00:03:08.647 --> 00:03:10.774
{\an8}If this place is dumb enough
to let us manipulate our DNA.

83
00:03:10.816 --> 00:03:12.734
{\an8}Morty. then we'll
just evolve our way out.

84
00:03:12.776 --> 00:03:13.902
{\an8}First step is fins.

85
00:03:13.944 --> 00:03:15.987
{\an8}Wait. How?

86
00:03:13.944 --> 00:03:15.987
{\an8}Mitosis. Morty.

87
00:03:16.029 --> 00:03:18.156
{\an8}Think really hard
about being your own daughter.

88
00:03:18.198 --> 00:03:19.157
[ Grunts ]

89
00:03:19.199 --> 00:03:20.158
[ Grunts ]

90
00:03:20.242 --> 00:03:21.993
[ Grunting continues ]

91
00:03:22.035 --> 00:03:26.331
{\an8}♪♪

92
00:03:26.415 --> 00:03:27.791
Being a fish isn't so bad.

93
00:03:27.833 --> 00:03:29.543
Swimming is fun.

94
00:03:29.626 --> 00:03:31.169
I do like
how you're never thirsty.

95
00:03:31.211 --> 00:03:32.963
And the whole world's
your toilet.

96
00:03:37.134 --> 00:03:39.052
[ Both gasping ]

97
00:03:39.136 --> 00:03:40.512
Oh. Oh. air.

98
00:03:39.136 --> 00:03:40.512
[ Gasping ]

99
00:03:40.554 --> 00:03:41.346
So good.

100
00:03:41.430 --> 00:03:42.889
[ Strained ] So good.

101
00:03:43.765 --> 00:03:45.016
[ Snake hisses ]

102
00:03:45.100 --> 00:03:46.727
[ Animals growl ]

103
00:03:47.185 --> 00:03:48.353
[ Gasps ]

104
00:03:49.020 --> 00:03:49.980
[ Groans ]

105
00:03:50.021 --> 00:03:51.982
[ Breathing heavily ]

106
00:03:52.816 --> 00:03:54.025
{\an8}Toughen up. Morty.

107
00:03:54.109 --> 00:03:55.610
{\an8}The primordial soup was
just the beginning.

108
00:03:55.694 --> 00:03:57.195
{\an8}We're in some kind of
hollow earth.

109
00:03:57.279 --> 00:03:59.322
{\an8}The reincarnation field
must be contained

110
00:03:59.364 --> 00:04:00.574
{\an8}within the warden's
root lattice.

111
00:04:00.657 --> 00:04:01.950
{\an8}If we escape to the surface.

112
00:04:02.033 --> 00:04:03.034
{\an8}we escape the cycle.

113
00:04:03.076 --> 00:04:04.119
[ Gasping ]

114
00:04:04.202 --> 00:04:05.537
[ Choking ]

115
00:04:05.579 --> 00:04:08.039
God damn it. Morty.
you're a lungfish.

116
00:04:08.081 --> 00:04:10.917
Use your lungs.

117
00:04:11.001 --> 00:04:12.461
[ Groans ]

118
00:04:13.420 --> 00:04:14.880
[ Groans ]

119
00:04:14.963 --> 00:04:17.007
[ Water burbles ]

120
00:04:19.426 --> 00:04:21.678
[ Orb whirs ]

121
00:04:24.139 --> 00:04:25.390
[ Water splashes ]

122
00:04:26.183 --> 00:04:27.684
{\an8}Sorry.

123
00:04:27.726 --> 00:04:29.144
{\an8}You know how much willpower
it takes to drown yourself?

124
00:04:29.227 --> 00:04:30.395
W-What do you want
to try next?

125
00:04:30.479 --> 00:04:32.731
I got eight words for you...

126
00:04:32.773 --> 00:04:34.733
legs.

127
00:04:34.775 --> 00:04:36.067
This is great.

128
00:04:36.109 --> 00:04:37.778
We let our food come to us
and plan our next move.

129
00:04:37.861 --> 00:04:39.404
{\an8}Um. I think I'm stuck.

130
00:04:39.488 --> 00:04:40.822
{\an8}In our own web?

131
00:04:40.906 --> 00:04:42.991
{\an8}It's fine.
I'll use you and pull myself up.

132
00:04:43.074 --> 00:04:44.075
[ Stammers ] Don't!

133
00:04:44.159 --> 00:04:45.577
{\an8}Oh!

134
00:04:44.159 --> 00:04:45.577
{\an8}Damn it!

135
00:04:45.619 --> 00:04:48.455
{\an8}[ Chuckles ]
Not so fun. is it?

136
00:04:48.538 --> 00:04:50.415
{\an8}Eat shit!

137
00:04:48.538 --> 00:04:50.415
{\an8}I'm gonna!

138
00:04:50.457 --> 00:04:52.334
{\an8}Morty.
I'm gonna evolve wings.

139
00:04:52.417 --> 00:04:53.960
{\an8}and then I'm gonna
kill that guy.

140
00:04:54.461 --> 00:04:55.462
[ Water splashes ]

141
00:04:55.545 --> 00:04:57.130
Morty: Whoo-hoo!

142
00:04:57.214 --> 00:04:58.673
This is amazing. Rick.

143
00:04:58.757 --> 00:05:00.258
And really quick to get to.

144
00:05:00.300 --> 00:05:02.177
Birds are basically
small dinosaurs.

145
00:05:02.761 --> 00:05:04.721
{\an8}All right. Morty.
there's no thermals.

146
00:05:04.763 --> 00:05:07.265
So we've got to evolve really
specific wings to get up there.

147
00:05:07.307 --> 00:05:08.934
{\an8}Oh. you can't build us
mech suits yet.

148
00:05:08.975 --> 00:05:10.685
{\an8}Nah. birds can get
wherever they want.

149
00:05:10.727 --> 00:05:12.479
{\an8}but can't do anything
once they get there.

150
00:05:12.562 --> 00:05:14.105
{\an8}It's like astral projection.

151
00:05:14.189 --> 00:05:15.315
[ Squawks ]

152
00:05:14.189 --> 00:05:15.315
Oh. shit!

153
00:05:15.398 --> 00:05:16.817
he can get us down here.
too.

154
00:05:16.900 --> 00:05:22.739
{\an8}♪♪

155
00:05:22.781 --> 00:05:24.741
{\an8}All right. Pretty obvious.

156
00:05:24.783 --> 00:05:26.243
{\an8}We gotta climb a tech tree
to climb the actual tree.

157
00:05:26.284 --> 00:05:28.495
{\an8}And we do that with...

158
00:05:28.578 --> 00:05:31.456
{\an8}Hands. Supple. grippy hands

159
00:05:31.540 --> 00:05:33.291
{\an8}and a pretty familiar version
of --

160
00:05:33.333 --> 00:05:36.127
{\an8}God. just go already.

161
00:05:33.333 --> 00:05:36.127
{\an8}Don't wait up!

162
00:05:36.211 --> 00:05:38.004
[ Imitating monkey squalls ]

163
00:05:41.091 --> 00:05:44.261
Um. this watering hole is
pretty tense.

164
00:05:44.302 --> 00:05:47.472
Pretty. um. ape heavy.

165
00:05:44.302 --> 00:05:47.472
Exactly.

166
00:05:47.556 --> 00:05:50.725
There's holes for apes only.
Clear out.

167
00:05:50.767 --> 00:05:53.311
Oh. we were just.
uh. drinking water.

168
00:05:53.395 --> 00:05:54.771
And using tools!

169
00:05:54.813 --> 00:05:57.482
Hey. look.
this guy's jerking off a stick

170
00:05:57.524 --> 00:05:58.567
with his rock

171
00:05:58.650 --> 00:06:00.193
He’s a stick stroker!

172
00:06:00.277 --> 00:06:01.945
I'm gonna end you. tool man.

173
00:06:01.987 --> 00:06:04.155
We. uh. we-we-we
we can move along.

174
00:06:04.197 --> 00:06:05.365
Argh!

175
00:06:05.448 --> 00:06:06.950
-[ Grunts ]
-[ Groans ]

176
00:06:06.992 --> 00:06:08.326
Oh. my God. Rick!

177
00:06:08.368 --> 00:06:09.494
Hey. what the fuck?

178
00:06:08.368 --> 00:06:09.494
Hey! Kill those monkeys

179
00:06:09.536 --> 00:06:10.579
slightly different than us.

180
00:06:10.662 --> 00:06:12.247
What are you doing. Rick?

181
00:06:12.330 --> 00:06:14.875
They started it. Domination
through technology. Morty.

182
00:06:14.958 --> 00:06:17.961
We're going apex.
This stick is your god!

183
00:06:18.003 --> 00:06:19.004
He's got a thing!

184
00:06:19.087 --> 00:06:20.297
[ Grunts ]

185
00:06:20.338 --> 00:06:21.298
{\an8}Oh!

186
00:06:21.339 --> 00:06:22.507
{\an8}Ri... Rick?

187
00:06:22.632 --> 00:06:23.758
{\an8}I'm doing this
for both of us.

188
00:06:23.842 --> 00:06:25.802
{\an8}I'll find you
when I find you.

189
00:06:29.681 --> 00:06:31.433
Guess he really did bail
on me.

190
00:06:31.516 --> 00:06:32.517
You lost. son?

191
00:06:32.559 --> 00:06:34.352
Oh. Oh. hey. Uh. please --

192
00:06:34.436 --> 00:06:36.146
Please don't kill me
for my cytoplasm.

193
00:06:36.187 --> 00:06:37.689
Oh. child.

194
00:06:37.731 --> 00:06:40.442
you've been trapped in
the cycle of violence too long.

195
00:06:40.483 --> 00:06:42.485
I don't know.
maybe you're right.

196
00:06:42.527 --> 00:06:44.279
I'm tired of fighting
all the time.

197
00:06:44.362 --> 00:06:45.947
Mm-hmm.

198
00:06:45.989 --> 00:06:48.533
I've seen countless souls
waste a billion lifetimes trying

199
00:06:48.575 --> 00:06:49.951
to bust out of here.

200
00:06:50.035 --> 00:06:51.745
But you can't fight
the cycle. son.

201
00:06:51.828 --> 00:06:54.456
You got to submit to it.
Serve nature.

202
00:06:54.539 --> 00:06:56.958
Is this where you kill me?

203
00:06:57.000 --> 00:06:59.336
Oh. you are traumatized.

204
00:06:59.377 --> 00:07:05.383
{\an8}♪♪

205
00:07:05.467 --> 00:07:06.885
Wow!

206
00:07:06.968 --> 00:07:08.553
Pollinating. building
little hexagon houses.

207
00:07:08.595 --> 00:07:10.305
feels good to do
something positive.

208
00:07:10.388 --> 00:07:11.306
All: Mm-hmm.

209
00:07:11.389 --> 00:07:12.724
You see?

210
00:07:12.766 --> 00:07:13.850
And I reckon the warden
likes it. too.

211
00:07:13.892 --> 00:07:15.852
What are you in for. Morty?

212
00:07:15.894 --> 00:07:18.897
I was a scout for an orc species
looking for planets to conquer.

213
00:07:18.939 --> 00:07:21.066
I was a scout
for a sludge species looking

214
00:07:21.149 --> 00:07:22.525
for planets to conquer.

215
00:07:22.567 --> 00:07:24.694
Well. I'm a touch different

216
00:07:24.736 --> 00:07:28.907
because I was a pod person
looking for planets to conquer.

217
00:07:28.949 --> 00:07:31.159
I was helping
my grandpa get sap.

218
00:07:31.242 --> 00:07:33.370
I assume it makes energy
or gets you high.

219
00:07:33.411 --> 00:07:34.663
I-I-I don't know.

220
00:07:34.746 --> 00:07:36.748
Aha. That adds up.

221
00:07:36.831 --> 00:07:39.918
He seems the type to be
locked in here. but you don't.

222
00:07:39.960 --> 00:07:41.002
Thank you!

223
00:07:41.086 --> 00:07:43.421
It's a... There's a...

224
00:07:43.463 --> 00:07:46.216
G-O-R...

225
00:07:47.008 --> 00:07:51.221
Should’ve... spelled... "ape."

226
00:07:51.262 --> 00:07:52.597
[ Water splashes ]

227
00:07:52.681 --> 00:07:54.057
On to the next one.

228
00:07:54.099 --> 00:07:56.434
Every cycle evolves
as closer to parole.

229
00:07:56.476 --> 00:07:58.395
[ Cheering ]

230
00:07:58.937 --> 00:08:02.774
Ohhhh. I'm so fucking wounded.

231
00:08:02.816 --> 00:08:03.942
Everyone follow my lead.

232
00:08:02.816 --> 00:08:03.942
Owwww.

233
00:08:03.984 --> 00:08:05.652
Your lead?
I'm the alpha.

234
00:08:05.735 --> 00:08:06.945
Dog. I'm the alpha.

235
00:08:07.028 --> 00:08:10.198
Easy prey here.
Easy pickings.

236
00:08:10.281 --> 00:08:11.241
Get em.

237
00:08:10.281 --> 00:08:11.241
Now!

238
00:08:11.282 --> 00:08:13.827
I'm the alpha.

239
00:08:11.282 --> 00:08:13.827
Omega!

240
00:08:13.910 --> 00:08:16.079
A hole? This isn't alpha at all.

241
00:08:16.121 --> 00:08:19.624
We're all betas now.
Come on. time to meet the boss.

242
00:08:19.666 --> 00:08:23.044
{\an8}♪♪

243
00:08:23.086 --> 00:08:26.256
Hey. I know usually I'd
be trying to eat you and all.

244
00:08:26.297 --> 00:08:27.799
but maybe Los Lobos in the herd.

245
00:08:27.882 --> 00:08:30.301
Hey!
No interspecies solidarity.

246
00:08:30.385 --> 00:08:35.682
{\an8}♪♪

247
00:08:35.765 --> 00:08:37.642
The wolves have
been incorporated. sir.

248
00:08:37.726 --> 00:08:39.853
All except for that one.

249
00:08:39.936 --> 00:08:42.313
I'm sorry for those things
I said about apes.

250
00:08:42.397 --> 00:08:44.190
More fermented berry mash.

251
00:08:44.274 --> 00:08:47.152
Right away. sir.

252
00:08:44.274 --> 00:08:47.152
It's time to climb this fucker.

253
00:08:47.193 --> 00:08:48.987
{\an8}♪♪

254
00:08:49.029 --> 00:08:50.697
[ Metal clangs ]

255
00:08:51.281 --> 00:08:52.490
[ Liquid hisses ]

256
00:08:52.532 --> 00:08:53.992
Listen up. pawns.

257
00:08:54.034 --> 00:08:56.077
We begin the task
of scaling this root.

258
00:08:56.161 --> 00:08:58.997
The root will kill you
if you touch it.

259
00:08:59.039 --> 00:09:01.833
You will go one at a time
for observation purposes.

260
00:09:01.916 --> 00:09:03.293
On. now.

261
00:09:03.334 --> 00:09:05.712
Kind of feel like I'm
being punished for my loyalty.

262
00:09:05.795 --> 00:09:07.505
Lead by example.
Gorilla #3.

263
00:09:07.589 --> 00:09:12.510
{\an8}♪♪

264
00:09:12.594 --> 00:09:18.349
{\an8}♪♪

265
00:09:18.433 --> 00:09:20.393
[ Gas hisses ]

266
00:09:20.477 --> 00:09:22.020
[ Groans ]

267
00:09:23.188 --> 00:09:24.481
Gas 20 feet up.

268
00:09:24.522 --> 00:09:26.024
Next!

269
00:09:28.193 --> 00:09:30.195
[ Distant screams ]

270
00:09:31.654 --> 00:09:33.239
[ Yells ]

271
00:09:33.323 --> 00:09:37.452
{\an8}♪♪

272
00:09:37.535 --> 00:09:38.828
You know what? Fine.

273
00:09:38.870 --> 00:09:41.206
If we can't break out.
we break him.

274
00:09:41.247 --> 00:09:48.213
{\an8}♪♪

275
00:09:48.254 --> 00:09:54.719
{\an8}♪♪

276
00:09:54.803 --> 00:09:57.055
[ Vines creak ]

277
00:09:58.640 --> 00:09:59.641
Ugh!

278
00:09:59.724 --> 00:10:03.394
{\an8}♪♪

279
00:10:03.478 --> 00:10:05.730
[ Fire hisses ]

280
00:10:06.606 --> 00:10:08.566
[ Thunder cracks ]

281
00:10:08.608 --> 00:10:13.404
{\an8}♪♪

282
00:10:13.446 --> 00:10:15.073
[ Grunts ]

283
00:10:16.574 --> 00:10:18.409
[ Soft music plays ]

284
00:10:18.451 --> 00:10:20.912
So we clean shit
from the ocean?

285
00:10:20.954 --> 00:10:22.747
Ocean needs cleanin'.

286
00:10:24.415 --> 00:10:26.543
And we shit in the ocean?

287
00:10:26.584 --> 00:10:28.169
Ocean needs shittin'.

288
00:10:32.006 --> 00:10:35.760
And we shit in the soil while
eating shit out of the soil?

289
00:10:35.844 --> 00:10:38.304
You're pretty hung up on
the shit part of it. aren't you?

290
00:10:38.388 --> 00:10:43.226
{\an8}♪♪

291
00:10:43.268 --> 00:10:44.936
What's troubling you. son?

292
00:10:44.978 --> 00:10:47.647
I mean. I like the
nonviolence. don't get me wrong.

293
00:10:47.730 --> 00:10:49.691
And having a shell is fun.

294
00:10:49.732 --> 00:10:52.026
but it just feels
like we're going in circles.

295
00:10:52.068 --> 00:10:54.612
Well. that's what
a healthy ecosystem is.

296
00:10:54.654 --> 00:10:56.364
Eventually. the warden
will notice

297
00:10:56.447 --> 00:10:57.991
our piety and set us free.

298
00:10:58.074 --> 00:11:00.827
Until then.
we find peace in here.

299
00:11:00.910 --> 00:11:03.621
So a reformed prisoner
is someone

300
00:11:03.705 --> 00:11:05.415
who doesn't want to leave
the prison?

301
00:11:05.456 --> 00:11:07.125
See? You get it.

302
00:11:07.167 --> 00:11:10.170
Oh. now you're probably
just hungry. Here.

303
00:11:10.253 --> 00:11:12.088
I guess I don't want to eat.
whoever that is.

304
00:11:12.130 --> 00:11:14.632
Now. son.
that's a vegetable.

305
00:11:14.716 --> 00:11:16.843
No one picks being a vegetable.

306
00:11:16.926 --> 00:11:20.096
you'd have to really give up
to be one of those.

307
00:11:20.930 --> 00:11:23.808
Hey. uh. I think
I'm maybe gonna brave the rest

308
00:11:23.850 --> 00:11:25.810
of this life alone.

309
00:11:25.894 --> 00:11:27.604
Well.
you know where to find us.

310
00:11:27.645 --> 00:11:29.147
We'll be eating shit.

311
00:11:29.189 --> 00:11:36.529
{\an8}♪♪

312
00:11:36.613 --> 00:11:38.698
[ Water thuds ]

313
00:11:39.824 --> 00:11:41.784
[ Sighs ]

314
00:11:41.826 --> 00:11:43.578
[ Grunts ]

315
00:11:43.661 --> 00:11:47.040
{\an8}♪♪

316
00:11:47.123 --> 00:11:48.166
Hmm.

317
00:11:48.249 --> 00:11:53.379
{\an8}♪♪

318
00:11:53.463 --> 00:11:54.422
Oh.

319
00:11:54.505 --> 00:12:00.428
{\an8}♪♪

320
00:12:00.511 --> 00:12:05.808
{\an8}♪♪

321
00:12:05.850 --> 00:12:08.519
{\an8}[ Shivering ]

322
00:12:08.561 --> 00:12:15.443
{\an8}♪♪

323
00:12:15.526 --> 00:12:17.320
[ Laughing ]

324
00:12:17.362 --> 00:12:25.620
{\an8}♪♪

325
00:12:25.703 --> 00:12:33.878
{\an8}♪♪

326
00:12:33.962 --> 00:12:35.296
[ Farts ]

327
00:12:35.380 --> 00:12:40.218
{\an8}♪♪

328
00:12:40.260 --> 00:12:41.427
{\an8}[ Farts ]

329
00:12:41.511 --> 00:12:48.226
{\an8}♪♪

330
00:12:48.268 --> 00:12:54.774
{\an8}♪♪

331
00:12:54.857 --> 00:13:01.572
{\an8}♪♪

332
00:13:01.614 --> 00:13:08.329
{\an8}♪♪

333
00:13:08.413 --> 00:13:09.664
[ Grunts ]

334
00:13:09.747 --> 00:13:12.041
{\an8}♪♪

335
00:13:12.083 --> 00:13:15.295
[ Gasps ] Sun! Real sun!

336
00:13:15.378 --> 00:13:17.088
[ Snoring ]

337
00:13:17.130 --> 00:13:20.091
Oh. great Warden! I did it!
I figured it out!

338
00:13:20.174 --> 00:13:22.927
The goal is to be a plant.
like you!

339
00:13:23.011 --> 00:13:24.804
Oh...

340
00:13:23.011 --> 00:13:24.804
Whoa.

341
00:13:24.887 --> 00:13:26.848
So many nutrients in the soil
up here.

342
00:13:26.931 --> 00:13:28.391
Y-Yes.
[ Clears throat ]

343
00:13:28.433 --> 00:13:32.729
The life cycles of
the guilty provide nourishment.

344
00:13:32.770 --> 00:13:34.063
Oh.

345
00:13:34.105 --> 00:13:35.732
But that's
more of a byproduct

346
00:13:35.773 --> 00:13:37.734
than the point of all this.
right?

347
00:13:37.775 --> 00:13:40.695
[ Chuckles ]

348
00:13:40.778 --> 00:13:44.157
So I-I live up here now?

349
00:13:44.240 --> 00:13:47.452
Oh. uh.
this is my spot.

350
00:13:47.535 --> 00:13:50.872
Okay. I-I ca-- I can go
find my own planet.

351
00:13:50.955 --> 00:13:52.999
Ahhh.

352
00:13:53.082 --> 00:13:56.544
You would kinda need to be
a spacefarer for that.

353
00:13:56.627 --> 00:13:58.129
And I don't like those.

354
00:13:58.171 --> 00:14:00.923
But now you know
how cool it is to be a tree.

355
00:14:00.965 --> 00:14:02.925
Oh.

356
00:14:00.965 --> 00:14:02.925
Boink!

357
00:14:02.967 --> 00:14:10.391
{\an8}♪♪

358
00:14:10.475 --> 00:14:17.315
{\an8}♪♪

359
00:14:17.398 --> 00:14:20.109
Okay. we have that
bronze post-mortem in 10.

360
00:14:20.151 --> 00:14:23.321
followed by the all hands
on opposable thumbs.

361
00:14:23.404 --> 00:14:25.656
[ Whistle! ]

362
00:14:25.698 --> 00:14:27.408
[ Thud! ]

363
00:14:29.494 --> 00:14:30.995
I'll reschedule.

364
00:14:32.663 --> 00:14:33.790
Look who it is.

365
00:14:33.873 --> 00:14:35.416
You don't have to do this.
man.

366
00:14:35.500 --> 00:14:37.543
The system's rigged. H-He
wants us fighting each other.

367
00:14:37.585 --> 00:14:40.546
Sounds like I'm on the
right side of history.

368
00:14:37.585 --> 00:14:40.546
Morty!

369
00:14:40.588 --> 00:14:42.048
[ Grunting ]

370
00:14:42.090 --> 00:14:43.549
Alright. Morty.
let's shake a leg.

371
00:14:43.591 --> 00:14:44.926
When he respawns
in a second.

372
00:14:44.967 --> 00:14:46.427
he's not gonna be
any less annoying.

373
00:14:46.469 --> 00:14:47.845
Rick?!
Is this a coincidence?

374
00:14:47.929 --> 00:14:49.555
Y-You died
at the same time as me?

375
00:14:49.597 --> 00:14:51.265
I saw everything.
buddy.

376
00:14:51.307 --> 00:14:52.683
You beat the system.
then the system beat back.

377
00:14:52.767 --> 00:14:54.560
Ugh!
He's -- He's evil. Rick!

378
00:14:54.602 --> 00:14:56.396
He's feeding off the cycle
of death!

379
00:14:56.437 --> 00:14:58.481
W-We're all just mulch!

380
00:14:58.564 --> 00:15:00.608
Damn.
Pretty diabolical tree.

381
00:15:00.691 --> 00:15:03.152
I don't wanna be mulch!
I wanna go home!

382
00:15:03.236 --> 00:15:04.570
We have to stop killing
each other!

383
00:15:04.612 --> 00:15:06.197
We will. buddy.

384
00:15:06.280 --> 00:15:08.074
No more death now.
That's what feeds the tree.

385
00:15:08.116 --> 00:15:10.535
I'm back!
[ Grunts ]

386
00:15:10.618 --> 00:15:13.454
After that.
Now let's go.

387
00:15:14.038 --> 00:15:18.209
NAAAAAAAAAAAANTS
ingonyamaaaaa bagithi baba...

388
00:15:18.292 --> 00:15:19.961
[ Coughs ]

389
00:15:20.002 --> 00:15:21.671
Thanks for indulging me.

390
00:15:21.754 --> 00:15:24.674
I'm not in the form of a lion.
but I did want to sing the song.

391
00:15:24.757 --> 00:15:26.634
Hello. inmates.

392
00:15:24.757 --> 00:15:26.634
[ Booing ]

393
00:15:26.676 --> 00:15:28.636
Okay. I deserve that.

394
00:15:28.678 --> 00:15:30.096
But I have something to say.

395
00:15:30.138 --> 00:15:32.306
{\an8}You expect us
to listen to you?!

396
00:15:32.390 --> 00:15:36.394
No. I expect you
to listen to Morty.

397
00:15:36.436 --> 00:15:39.647
The Warden seems wise and stoic.
but he's just a big tree.

398
00:15:39.730 --> 00:15:41.607
Which means we can starve him
out!

399
00:15:41.649 --> 00:15:43.943
It's a hunger strike!
But for him.

400
00:15:43.985 --> 00:15:47.321
We'll all live peacefully
in a contained system.

401
00:15:47.405 --> 00:15:49.657
So instead of escaping.

402
00:15:49.740 --> 00:15:52.326
we'll live in a smaller.
shittier prison?

403
00:15:52.368 --> 00:15:53.327
I didn't say shittier!

404
00:15:53.369 --> 00:15:54.829
Gorilla 3. is that you?

405
00:15:54.871 --> 00:15:57.582
It's Hyena 3 now.
I got a new job.

406
00:15:57.665 --> 00:15:59.000
Seems like
a lateral step.

407
00:15:59.041 --> 00:16:01.127
Th-Think of it more
as a biodome.

408
00:16:01.169 --> 00:16:03.838
You've spent a million
lifetimes being dogs and fish.

409
00:16:03.921 --> 00:16:06.632
It won't kill you
to spend one lifetime on this.

410
00:16:06.674 --> 00:16:10.344
Hopefully nothing will kill you.
That's the point of the strike.

411
00:16:10.386 --> 00:16:12.472
[ All murmuring ]

412
00:16:12.513 --> 00:16:17.894
{\an8}♪♪

413
00:16:17.977 --> 00:16:21.522
Oh. this was a mistake.

414
00:16:17.977 --> 00:16:21.522
What? This looks great!

415
00:16:21.606 --> 00:16:24.192
Then again.
I am a bat.

416
00:16:24.275 --> 00:16:26.027
Welcome to ME!

417
00:16:26.068 --> 00:16:27.695
Combined with Morty's
plant-based livin'.

418
00:16:27.737 --> 00:16:29.697
we should all age
pretty gracefully.

419
00:16:29.739 --> 00:16:31.616
All he needs from you is...

420
00:16:31.699 --> 00:16:33.201
Hey. Mornin'.

421
00:16:33.242 --> 00:16:35.703
Shittin' hard
or hardly shittin'?

422
00:16:33.242 --> 00:16:35.703
[ Laughs ]

423
00:16:35.786 --> 00:16:37.955
Ya know. when they pitched me
on this herbivore diet.

424
00:16:38.039 --> 00:16:40.541
I was skeptical.
but then I tried the pizza.

425
00:16:40.625 --> 00:16:42.502
[ Both laugh ]

426
00:16:42.543 --> 00:16:49.842
{\an8}♪♪

427
00:16:49.884 --> 00:16:57.350
{\an8}♪♪

428
00:16:57.391 --> 00:17:04.690
{\an8}♪♪

429
00:17:04.732 --> 00:17:11.822
{\an8}♪♪

430
00:17:11.906 --> 00:17:13.574
I need 34 bruschettas.
all day.

431
00:17:13.616 --> 00:17:15.034
Yes. Chimp!

432
00:17:16.077 --> 00:17:17.870
And you laugh
at all my jokes.

433
00:17:17.912 --> 00:17:21.165
It's true. it's true.

434
00:17:21.249 --> 00:17:23.167
I led us all down here
with the expressed purpose

435
00:17:23.209 --> 00:17:25.169
of killing our tree
warden overlord.

436
00:17:25.253 --> 00:17:27.380
which I remind you is
still our goal.

437
00:17:27.421 --> 00:17:29.173
He should actually be
pretty weak by now.

438
00:17:29.257 --> 00:17:32.093
However. I knew we were putting
down roots.

439
00:17:32.176 --> 00:17:34.095
but never imagined
love would bloom.

440
00:17:34.178 --> 00:17:36.222
What doesn't bloom
down here?

441
00:17:36.264 --> 00:17:37.598
[ Laughter ]

442
00:17:37.682 --> 00:17:40.268
Ha ha ha. congratulations!

443
00:17:40.309 --> 00:17:42.770
Hyena 3 and Sheep.
you may now --

444
00:17:42.853 --> 00:17:45.565
Okay. already doing it.
Hot.

445
00:17:45.606 --> 00:17:47.858
[ Cheering ]

446
00:17:47.942 --> 00:17:50.278
Ho-ho. let's par-tay!

447
00:17:50.361 --> 00:17:54.365
[ Cheering ]

448
00:17:57.368 --> 00:17:58.786
Ohhh.

449
00:17:58.869 --> 00:18:02.623
I'm so...hungry.

450
00:18:02.665 --> 00:18:06.377
Wh-What's happening down there?

451
00:18:08.254 --> 00:18:12.008
Hey! Start killing each other!

452
00:18:12.091 --> 00:18:16.304
Hello? Anybody?

453
00:18:16.387 --> 00:18:20.141
Oh. you little fuckers
are gonna get it now!

454
00:18:31.027 --> 00:18:33.446
"Get bent."

455
00:18:33.487 --> 00:18:36.574
Get bent?
Little toothless.

456
00:18:36.657 --> 00:18:37.825
Not that I can beat it.

457
00:18:37.867 --> 00:18:39.243
Now!

458
00:18:40.536 --> 00:18:41.787
Aaaaah!

459
00:18:41.829 --> 00:18:43.748
[ Grunting ]

460
00:18:43.831 --> 00:18:48.502
{\an8}♪♪

461
00:18:48.586 --> 00:18:50.963
It's working. He's too weak
to get us with his vines!

462
00:18:51.005 --> 00:18:53.466
Good thing. too.
I didn't anticipate how old

463
00:18:53.507 --> 00:18:56.177
and pacified our forces would be
by the time this plan worked.

464
00:18:56.218 --> 00:18:58.471
Come on. Hyena 3.
marriage made ya soft.

465
00:18:58.512 --> 00:19:01.474
Leave him alone!

466
00:18:58.512 --> 00:19:01.474
You were always a toxic boss!

467
00:19:02.475 --> 00:19:04.060
[ Grunts ]

468
00:19:04.143 --> 00:19:06.646
It's working! Phase 2 now!

469
00:19:06.687 --> 00:19:12.818
{\an8}♪♪

470
00:19:12.860 --> 00:19:18.949
{\an8}♪♪

471
00:19:19.033 --> 00:19:20.076
Pull!

472
00:19:20.159 --> 00:19:21.952
[ All grunting ]

473
00:19:22.036 --> 00:19:23.496
{\an8}♪♪

474
00:19:23.537 --> 00:19:24.705
No!

475
00:19:24.747 --> 00:19:28.084
This planet was
my retirement!

476
00:19:28.167 --> 00:19:29.794
Say it with me. animals!

477
00:19:29.877 --> 00:19:32.296
All: Timber!

478
00:19:32.380 --> 00:19:36.967
{\an8}♪♪

479
00:19:38.427 --> 00:19:43.391
[ Weakly ] Doesn't anybody hate
anybody anymore?

480
00:19:43.432 --> 00:19:47.895
Hey. birds. don't snakes
always eat your eggs?

481
00:19:47.937 --> 00:19:49.438
Don't --
Don't fall for that.

482
00:19:49.522 --> 00:19:52.858
Come on.
Someone's gotta have a grudge.

483
00:19:52.900 --> 00:19:54.860
This is too reformed!

484
00:19:54.902 --> 00:19:57.154
Oh. did we evolve
too much?

485
00:19:57.196 --> 00:20:01.492
I-I actually have
deep respect for spacefarers.

486
00:20:01.575 --> 00:20:04.537
Parked your ships all nice
and neat up there.

487
00:20:06.580 --> 00:20:08.499
If it makes you feel
any better.

488
00:20:08.541 --> 00:20:11.252
I didn't steal anything
from the glove boxes!

489
00:20:11.335 --> 00:20:17.717
No! I'm dying!
Plants rule...

490
00:20:17.758 --> 00:20:20.428
[ Cheering ]

491
00:20:23.431 --> 00:20:25.599
{\an8}So...that --
that's it. then?

492
00:20:25.683 --> 00:20:29.478
I kinda thought we'd be returned
to our original bodies.

493
00:20:29.562 --> 00:20:32.440
No. no. no. no. we will.
We all just gotta believe.

494
00:20:32.481 --> 00:20:35.025
Yeah. we all just gotta
close our eyes.

495
00:20:35.109 --> 00:20:38.988
{\an8}Mm. okay.
You guys got us this far.

496
00:20:47.163 --> 00:20:48.956
{\an8}I don't feel anything.
Is it happening?

497
00:20:48.998 --> 00:20:50.624
Oh. it totally is.

498
00:20:50.666 --> 00:20:53.085
Ya gotta -- Ya gotta
keep those eyes tight. though.

499
00:20:53.127 --> 00:20:54.545
{\an8}You sound farther away.

500
00:20:54.587 --> 00:20:57.131
Ohh! My leaf became a hand!
It's working!

501
00:20:57.214 --> 00:20:58.924
{\an8}Hope that happens
to me.

502
00:20:58.966 --> 00:21:01.135
Rick: Whoa! Yeah! Ohhhh.

503
00:21:01.218 --> 00:21:05.139
Oh. ho. oh. it's so magical.

504
00:21:06.599 --> 00:21:09.977
{\an8}Interesting how it happened
to them first.

505
00:21:10.019 --> 00:21:12.813
-Yeah!
-Hoo. hoo. hoo!

506
00:21:15.024 --> 00:21:16.567
[ Both sigh ]

507
00:21:17.234 --> 00:21:19.195
Where have you two been
all day?

508
00:21:19.278 --> 00:21:21.489
Nunya.

509
00:21:19.278 --> 00:21:21.489
What's that? Biology?

510
00:21:21.572 --> 00:21:24.658
I think I know a thing
or two about that.

511
00:21:27.077 --> 00:21:27.995
Nope.

512
00:21:28.078 --> 00:21:35.836
{\an8}♪♪

513
00:21:35.878 --> 00:21:43.677
{\an8}♪♪

514
00:21:43.719 --> 00:21:51.477
{\an8}♪♪

515
00:21:51.519 --> 00:21:59.360
{\an8}♪♪

516
00:22:02.530 --> 00:22:05.157
Op! Excuse us.

517
00:22:02.530 --> 00:22:05.157
Huh.

518
00:22:05.199 --> 00:22:07.368
Dude.

519
00:22:05.199 --> 00:22:07.368
That was totally Hyena #3.

520
00:22:07.409 --> 00:22:09.078
Guess people got out.
huh?

521
00:22:09.161 --> 00:22:11.580
That is not
how I pictured him looking.

522
00:22:11.664 --> 00:22:13.123
Thanks. hon.

523
00:22:13.207 --> 00:22:16.335
This might sound crazy. but do
you know who I think I just saw?

524
00:22:16.377 --> 00:22:18.379
Was it the old man and boy
